Re: Internet Over Radio (IOR)
by sanddbox on Sun May 09, 2010 2:24 am	([msg=38463]see Re: Internet Over Radio (IOR)[/msg])
That sounds like a really interesting idea.However, if what you're talking about is to use it for web browsing, how could you request a webpage? That's the problem with radio; it's a connectionless protocol - you just send out waves and hope they get heard. There's no way to communicate back.I guess you did mention that it would have no interactivity.The thing is; what would this enable? We would be able to have long distance internet...but no way to request a webpage. It would be pretty interesting to see radio-based file transfer, though...
